    "name": "Urannag",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Urannags have long vexed scholars, some of whom contend that they\u2019re creatures, while others argue that they\u2019re complex traps. In truth, they\u2019re both\u2014an unsettling example of how reality on the Abyss doesn\u2019t match mortal expectations. An urannag behaves like an ambush predator, yet has no need for sustenance and is driven to f lense prey out of innate sadism."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>What at first appeared to be a sadistic spiked cage writhes into unholy life, extending bladed, articulated arms.</i>",
